template.description:
QuerySolr ranger_audits collection periodically (defined by CRON expression), apply transformation to conform to syslog format, and use PutTCP to bulk send audit records to Syslog server.
3 HBase table used here for book-keeping. (1) trigger table define the solr query evtTime range. It will be updated after every Solr query. (2) History table keep records of the successful Solr queries. (3) Solr_errrotable keep records of the failed Solr queries.
template.name: ranger_audits_2_syslog_0716

config.comments: Evaluate json document, get "interval" and "start_time" fields and put them in attributes.

To start, insert a trigger row in HBase table ranger_audits_syslog:trigger.
rowkey="trigger" column family is "cf" 2 columns: "start_time": value is a timestamp, format is yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ss.SSS'Z' "interval": value is milli-seconds.
For example: put 'ranger_audits_syslog:trigger', "trigger", 'cf:start_time', "2021-04-21T00:02:00.000Z" put 'ranger_audits_syslog:trigger', "trigger", 'cf:interval', "60000"
This processor retrieve the row and generate a flowfile like following: {"interval":"60000", "start_time":"2021-04-21T00:02:00.000Z"}
